-- string-split-join-crystal.cell: split string into words, rejoin with comma
-- Tests: split/join primitives, crystallization

⊢ transform
  given text ≡ "one two three four"
  yield result

  ∴ Split «text» by spaces, then rejoin with commas.

  ⊨ result = "one,two,three,four"

⊢ crystallize
  given §transform
  given transform→result
  yield §transform', is-faithful

  ∴ Read «§transform». It splits text on spaces and joins with commas.
    Write a ⊢= expression: join(split(text, " "), ",")
    Return the crystallized definition and faithfulness.

⊢ verify-crystal
  given §transform'
  given crystallize→is-faithful
  yield approved

  ∴ Does «§transform'» produce "one,two,three,four" for "one two three four"?

  ⊨ approved = true
